comments.body:
@nalind or @rhatdan I need some help here.  For buildah-in-podman (super-privileged as in PAPR) intg. testing in F30 I'm missing something (a CLI option or sysctl or something on the host).  How do I prevent https://cirrus-ci.com/task/6256151280222208?command=integration_test#L3274 ?

(all other tests mostly seem to be running well)

I'm running the container with various values for `$BUILDAH_ISOLATION` from here:  https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/1848/files#diff-a724b9731c5e35d731b550c9714775e1R189-R206

@rhatdan @vrothberg So this is not something I like about bors.  It's waiting a full two-hours for the underlying checks to pass, even if they fail after 20-minutes.  In this specific case it's the gate job failing (I know by clicking the red X mark in:

```
@bors Merge #1848 …                                       verified  X  932f6d4
```

Looking at the output, it is the `make validate` which is timing out, after about 10-minutes (must be setting somewhere to control this and verbosity?)

I'm looking at `./tests/validate/git-validation.sh`
